00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:16,000
 Hello, and welcome to my virtual office hours where I try to help you work through various kinds of Django, broken Django applications that you're running on Python Anywhere as part of my Django for everybody effort.

2
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:34,000
 So there's two basic errors that you run into, and you run into them because you're coding along in your thing, you save a file, you hit the reload button, and then something's not working the way you expect it.

3
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:44,000
 The sort of most frustrating thing is the startup failure, and this is where you see the something went wrong when you navigate to your application on Python Anywhere.

4
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:52,000
 What this really said is we're trying to get your application started, and we have failed in doing that, and we don't know what to do.

5
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:01,000
 We can't show your application because it doesn't run. Your application is so broken that Python Anywhere can't even start it.

6
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:15,000
 So you can start an application, and if you start it, you can still have bugs or problems in your application, and those are these yellow screens, the trace back, and you'll get used to learning these yellow screens.

7
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:32,000
 Some of them are easier to solve than others, and sometimes the answer is right there in front of you, like it is in this one that says, hey, line 6 and views.py is wrong, and it tells you what's wrong, that HTTPS response is not defined.

8
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:51,000
 And then sort of other times you've got to scroll up and down, and you've got to pass tracebacks and ignore this stuff and kind of read between the lines. It's part of programming, these things called tracebacks, especially when you're using a library like Django.

9
00:01:51,000 --> 00:02:07,000
 There's a bunch of library code that it's deep in a light piece of library code using something you've given it, and it blows up, and you kind of got to figure out where it is that your part starts and their part ends, and it's a little bit tricky.

